data.title: Your baby has too many names, Spanish duke told
data.meta_description: Sofía Fernanda Dolores Cayetana Teresa Ángela de la Cruz Micaela del Santísimo Sacramento del Perpetuo Socorro de la Santísima Trinidad y de Todos Los Santos has been baptised
data.text:
Over the centuries the dukes and duchesses of Alba have been accused of committing atrocities, plotting a coup and having extramarital affairs with bullfighters. To that can be added crimes against the environment, after a prosecutor alleged on Wednesday that one of the family, Eugenia Martínez de Irujo, Duchess of Montoro, was using “illegal wells” that draw water away from the ailing Doñana National Park in southern Spain.

Now, to pile on a further problem, Spain’s most senior aristocratic dynasty stands accused of another excess: giving its youngest member too many names to be legally registered.
